Lauretta Onye, a gold medalist at the Rio 2016 Paralympic Games, says athletes are unhappy over the recent dissolution of the sports federations by the dissolution of federations by the sports ministry. She described the move as an unnecessary distraction ahead of Tokyo 2020 Olympics. Onye, the Paralympic champion in the women’s F40 shot put event said, “The dissolution of federations is a distraction for the athletes and this is not good for the nation. “It is sad that something of this nature is happening now and the athletes are not happy. The Olympic Games is just around the corner, is this what we should be hearing?”.” Copyright PUNCH. All rights reserved. This material, and other digital content on this website, may not be reproduced, published, broadcast, rewritten or redistributed in whole or in part without prior express written permission from PUNCH. Contact: theeditor@punchng.com